        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 9:12AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 912 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Duffys Bend, or 9 miles southwest of Greensboro, moving east at 40
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Uniontown, Newbern, Arcola, Greensboro Municipal Airport, Perry
County Correctional Center, Gallion, Cedarville, and Laneville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
